cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the potential of network coding to improve network performance. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as network coding is a concept rooted in information theory. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is mentioned as one of the benefits of network coding in the abstract, so it is a possible category. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is mentioned in the abstract as a way to resolve deployment and orchestration problems using Software Defined Networking (SDN), so it is also a possible category. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible as network coding can be used in distributed computing scenarios.
